description.p:
Aspect 1. A method comprising:
withdrawing a first quantity of the gas from a gas source;
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a first thermal capacitor wherein the first thermal capacitor has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of a first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the first thermal capacitor;
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a second thermal capacitor wherein the second thermal capacitor has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of the first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the second thermal capacitor, wherein the first quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
heating or cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a third thermal capacitor wherein the third thermal capacitor has a temperature within the first target temperature range, wherein the first quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor; and
introducing the first quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor into a first receiving vessel, the first quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range.

Aspect 3. The method of aspect 1 or aspect 2 further comprising:
withdrawing a second quantity of the gas from the gas source;
cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor, wherein the second quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
heating or cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the third thermal capacitor wherein the third thermal capacitor has a temperature within the first target temperature range, wherein the second quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor; and
introducing the second quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor into a second receiving vessel, the second quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range.

Aspect 9. The method of any one of aspects 1 to 8 further comprising:
withdrawing a third quantity of the gas from the gas source;
cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor, wherein the third quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
heating or cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with a fourth thermal capacitor wherein the fourth thermal capacitor has a temperature within a second target temperature range, wherein the second target temperature range is different than the first target temperature range, and wherein the third quantity of gas exchanges heat with the fourth thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor; and
introducing the third quantity of gas from the fourth thermal capacitor into a third receiving vessel, the third quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the second target temperature range.

Aspect 10. The method of any one of aspects 1 to 9 further comprising:
measuring an ambient temperature representative of conditions surrounding a fourth receiving vessel;
withdrawing a fourth quantity of the gas from the gas source;
cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor, wherein the fourth quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
heating or cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with one of the third thermal capacitor and a fourth thermal capacitor, the third thermal capacitor having its temperature within the first temperature range, the fourth thermal capacitor having its temperature within the second temperature range, wherein the second target temperature range is different than the first target temperature range, and wherein the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the one of the third thermal capacitor and the fourth thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor, the selection of heating or cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the third thermal capacitor or the fourth thermal capacitor dependent upon the measured ambient temperature surrounding the fourth receiving vessel; and
introducing the fourth quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor or from the fourth thermal capacitor into the fourth receiving vessel, the fourth quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range when the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor or having a dispensing temperature within the second target temperature range when the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the fourth thermal capacitor.

Aspect 20. A method comprising:
withdrawing a first quantity of the gas from a gas source;
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a first thermal capacitor wherein the first thermal capacitor has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of a first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the first thermal capacitor;
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a second thermal capacitor wherein the second thermal capacitor has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of the first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the second thermal capacitor, wherein the first quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor;
providing a third thermal capacitor and a fourth thermal capacitor;
heating or cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with one of the third thermal capacitor and the fourth thermal capacitor wherein the third thermal capacitor has a temperature within the first target temperature range and the fourth thermal capacitor has a temperature within a second target temperature range which is different than the first target temperature range and may in particular comprise temperatures above the first target temperature range, wherein the first quantity of gas exchanges heat with the one of the third thermal capacitor and the fourth thermal capacitor after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor; and
introducing the first quantity of gas from the one of the third thermal capacitor and the fourth thermal capacitor into a first receiving vessel, the first quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor and having a dispensing temperature within the second target temperature range when the first quantity of gas exchanges heat with the fourth thermal capacitor.

claim.claim-text:
A method for dispensing a gas, the method comprising:
withdrawing a first quantity of the gas from a gas source (7);
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a first thermal capacitor (101) wherein the first thermal capacitor (101) has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of a first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the first thermal capacitor (101);
cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a second thermal capacitor (103) wherein the second thermal capacitor (103) has a temperature lower than the minimum temperature of the first target temperature range when the first quantity of gas is initially cooled by the second thermal capacitor (103), wherein the first quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103) after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
heating or cooling the first quantity of gas via heat exchange with a third thermal capacitor (107) wherein the third thermal capacitor (107) has a temperature within the first target temperature range, wherein the first quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor (107) after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103); and
introducing the first quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor (107) into a first receiving vessel, the first quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range.

The method of any one of the preceding claims further comprising:
withdrawing a second quantity of the gas from the gas source (7);
cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103), wherein the second quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103) after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
heating or cooling the second quantity of gas via heat exchange with the third thermal capacitor (107) wherein the third thermal capacitor (107) has a temperature within the first target temperature range, wherein the second quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor (107) after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103); and
introducing the second quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor (107) into a second receiving vessel, the second quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range.

The method of any one of the preceding claims further comprising:
withdrawing a third quantity of the gas from the gas source (7);
cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103), wherein the third quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103) after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
heating or cooling the third quantity of gas via heat exchange with a fourth thermal capacitor (207) wherein the fourth thermal capacitor (207) has a temperature within a second target temperature range, wherein the second target temperature range is different than the first target temperature range, and wherein the third quantity of gas exchanges heat with the fourth thermal capacitor (207) after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103); and
introducing the third quantity of gas from the fourth thermal capacitor (207) into a third receiving vessel, the third quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the second target temperature range.

The method of any one of the preceding claims further comprising:
measuring an ambient temperature representative of conditions surrounding a fourth receiving vessel;
withdrawing a fourth quantity of the gas from the gas source (7);
cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103), wherein the fourth quantity of gas is cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103) after being cooled via heat exchange with the first thermal capacitor (101);
heating or cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with one of the third thermal capacitor (107) and a fourth thermal capacitor (207), the third thermal capacitor (107) having its temperature within the first target temperature range, the fourth thermal capacitor (207) having its temperature within a second target temperature range, wherein the second target temperature range is different than the first target temperature range, and wherein the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the one of the third thermal capacitor (101) and the fourth thermal capacitor (207) after being cooled via heat exchange with the second thermal capacitor (103), the selection of heating or cooling the fourth quantity of gas via heat exchange with the third thermal capacitor (107) or the fourth thermal capacitor (207) being dependent upon the measured ambient temperature surrounding the fourth receiving vessel; and
introducing the fourth quantity of gas from the third thermal capacitor (107) or from the fourth thermal capacitor (207) into the fourth receiving vessel, the fourth quantity of gas thereby having a dispensing temperature within the first target temperature range when the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the third thermal capacitor (107) or having a dispensing temperature within the second target temperature range when the fourth quantity of gas exchanges heat with the fourth thermal capacitor (207).
